There are six chapters in Ephesians. Commands come in chapter 4, 5, and 6. In light of who we are, who are we to do.

<<<
I therefore, a prisoner for the Lord, urge you to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which you have been called,
<<<
''Ephesians 4:1''

Here we see the vindication of what we should do as Christians.

The very first thing that Paul tells us and reminds us is the following:

"There is one body and one Spirit - just as you were called to the one hope that belongs to your call- one Lord, one faith, one baptism, one God and Father of all, who is over all and through all and in all."

The Gospel takes hold of your life and changes who you are. As believers as Christ, we should never be complacent. Simply somewhere we can be content is never the case. A slow uphill climb towards Christ.

<<<
Now this I say and testify in the Lord, that you must no longer walk as the Gentiles do, in the futility of their minds. They are darkened in their understanding, alienated from the life of God because of the ignorance that is in them, due to their hardness of hear.
