All of these quotes, and more, we see this common theme of Ephesians that we have to come to the conclusion of what we say. God cares about the words that come out of our mouths. It isn't about just changing behavior. It isn't just talking to your younger self. Not just, you need to stop doing something different. It is a deeper issue than that. That out of the overflow of the mouth the heart speaks. What comes out of the mouth is a reflection of what comes out of our hearts.

We don't have the excuse to say that I know that I said that but that is not what mean. It is truly who you are. The reason you said it is because of what is going on in your heart. That is who you are.

There is a time for joking around, silly, and that is about it. Do you want to go 4 years in college and be known as that? I want to go talk to someone who is encouraging, build up, and speaks life for my life. This is a deeper issue than just that.

There is a way that you are not supposed to walk. It is a deeper issue. It is a worship issue. God cares about what we say to each other because what he has accomplished in us in our hearts. This must effect our words.

Two Characteristic About Christian Speech

!! A Christian Speech is not Corrupting
"Let no corrupting talk come out of your mouths [...]"

Let every corrupting word not come out of your mouth. Every word that is corrupting should be exercised from our life. The Greek word here is "sappros" unwholesome, rotten, and decaying.

You want to know about what God's estimation that cut people down? The gossip, slander, hateful speech, etc. The word used is like drinking from a jar of milk that has been rotten. Putrid, foul, rotten, etc.

This is the opposite of what would build up. Insulting speech, hateful speech, gossip speech, profane speech, crude joking, etc. These are the kinds of things that will tear the body down. Even through flattery (Psalm 55:21) (Proverbs 19:21 Proverbs 5:33 Proverbs 16:27)

Gossip is a problem. Word travels really fast at LBC. That morsel on our tongue tastes so good. Kind of sounds like James, it only takes a spark to get a fire going. James will go as far as to say, it is set on fire like hell. Our words have the power to destroy people. We wield it and we destroy people with it.

