!! Christian Speech Should be Edifying

<<
[...] but only such as is good for building up as fits the occasion, that it may give grace to those who hear.
<<<
''Ephesians 4:29''

The word "good" is kakas which is a specific teacher. There is none good but God. Not some inherent goodness. But we are talking about falling under the standard of God's perfection. Now that we are in Christ, that is what should characterize us. God is good and He is the one that demonstrates goodness.

When we desire good things for our brother, sisters, and Christs, it is why we need His grace. We want to be like Christ? Start here and start with your words.

You want to find someone who can control words, he can control his body. How huge of an animal can be steered by such a small ship in the mouth. But then he goes on to say it is impossible apart from Christ.

<<<
So, every healthy tree bears good fruit, but the diseased tree bears bad fruit. A healthy tree cannot bear bad fruit, nor can a diseased tree bear good fruit. Every tree that does not bear good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire. Thus you will recognize them by their fruits.
<<<
''Matthew 7:17-20''

You want to understand if something is good, look at what proceeds from their life. Christian speech is good for the purpose of building up. Building up of each other should be a great concern for a Christian.

Romans 15:2; 1 Corinthians 8:1; 1 Corinthians 14:12; 26

It is all about the body, building each up. Building each other stronger. A chain is only as strong as its weakest link. Work on not being the weakest link. If you are going through sin, you can find help from others. But don't remain from that place. Otherwise your structure will break. There is not passage in Scripture that just says build yourself up.

<<<
as fits the occasion, that it may give grace to those who hear.
<<<

We may not know whether or not the encouraging word is the best time. Someone may have had a rough need. Last thing they might need is a funny speech. The church isn't a place that we should be torn down even more. Beaten down. Coming to church should be life giving. It is always fitting for the occasion.

